UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS, BOVINE - COLOMBIA: (BOLIVAR), REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Fri 20 Aug 2010
Source: Magangue Hoy [in Spanish, trans. & summ., Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ, edited]
<http://maganguehoy.com/index.php?pagina=mostrar&Ed=3353-1>


There is great concern among cattle ranchers in the municipalities of
Tiquisio and Achi [Bolivar department] because of the sudden death of
57 heads of cattle in less than 15 days. The information was provided
by local people, who said that yesterday [20 Aug 2010] in a farm in
the locality of Puerto Coca [municipality of Tiquisio], 27 heads of
cattle from a total of 230 animals that arrived from Sincerin
[municipality of Achi] 15 days ago died in less than 24 hours.

In addition, 30 animals also brought from Sincerin, died 2 weeks ago
in Playa de Barro (Puerto Venecia, Achi). The cattle ranchers in the
area said that the animals had been vaccinated against FMD, triple,
and brucellosis, during the 1st vaccination cycle in 2010 [3 May-16 Jun 2010].

Heavy rains have affected the area and ranchers have had to move
their animals from flood prone areas to higher ground.

Veterinarian Manuel Hernandez Arrieta, director of Tiquisio's UMATA
[Municipal Unit of Agricultural Technical Assistance], traveled to
the affected farm and collected the required samples, which were sent
to the sectional ICA [Instituto Colombiano Agropecuario -- Colombian
Agricultural Institute] in Magangue for analysis to determine the
cause of death.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
