******
[2]
Date: Tue 24 Aug 2010
Source: RCN Radio [in Spanish trans. & summ. Corr.SB]
<http://www.rcnradio.com/noticias/locales/24-08-10/intoxicaci-n-masiva-mat-36-reces-en-el-sur-de-bol-var>


Massive intoxication has killed 36 cattle in southern Bolivar
department, Colombia.

"We have so far ruled out, any contagious disease such as FMD," said
Alvaro Monterrosa, director of the ICA in this region.

At least 36 heads of cattle have died in a case of mass intoxication
in a rural area of the municipality of Tiquisio, South Bolivar.

Monterrosa said it appeared the animals consumed a marine plant that
causes serious poisoning.

[Byline: Juan Carlos Ceron M]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The articles do not tell us what other infectious or contagious
diseases other than FMD have been ruled out.

While plant intoxications are known to occur, and can kill large
numbers of animals, I am uncertain what marine plant may be involved.
This area of Colombia has had abundant rains. Toxic plants may easily
have grown, or been stressed, or have seeded, and all of this may
make a plant toxic.

More information on this outbreak from knowledgeable sources in the
region would be gratefully appreciated. - Mods.TG/MPP]

[The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Colombia is available
at <http://healthmap.org/r/03HG>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
